, it is a 35/35 2h sword with 25AC, and some other meaningless stats (mana, yay).<br>
<br>
The reason I ask, is that for agro reasons, 1h is obviously the preferred way.  Which sucks, because the concept of a warrior using a nice big 2hander is very interesting to me.  However, this sword looks like it might be able to hit frequently enough and do enough damage to hold agro... but I don't have the resources to pick one up on a whim (30k on Inny). <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I just know that my monk, using a Tstaff, holds agro very nicely, even when the proc is being stubborn.<br>
<br>
Currently I am using the old Frostbringer/Snowchipper combo, which is nice and all... but kinda wussy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If I knew I could hold agro decently with the Wideblade (assisted by the fact that my guild knows what they are doing when it comes to agro management, I guess I'm a lucky warrior), I would gladly trade the FB and SC for it.<br>
<br>
Anyway... any feedback would be super. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Thanks in advance!<br>
